<dt-example table-type="html-wide" order="1">

<css lib="datatables searchpanes select" />
<js lib="jquery datatables searchpanes select">
<![CDATA[

$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            threshold: 0.4,
        },
    });
});

]]>
</js>

<title lib="searchPanes">Uniqueness Threshold for Individual Column</title>

<info><![CDATA[

This is the searchPanes extension for DataTables. It allows results to be filtered based on the values of columns.

This example shows how the definition of the `threshold` config option allows the user to define the level of uniqueness for a pane to be displayed.
The `threshold` of uniqueness is the number of unique values throughout the table divided by the total number of values.

The default of `threshold` is 0.6
]]></info>

